Bad smells can be a nightmare. It can come from the fridge because of power failure or from fruits and vegetables that have been kept longer than their shelf life. It could be smell from garbage cans due to accumulated rubbish evacuated late by the environmental agency. Here are few tricks to get rid of bad smells. Baking soda with water Photo credit Pinterest Lemons on grey wooden background Photo-credit_Greek Boston Clean the garbage can and place lemon or orange peels inside it. Directly Above Shot Of Roasted Coffee Beans In Cup And On Table Sprinkle a generous amount of ground coffee in the garbage. It can help to get rid of bad smells.
Vinegar can also be used to dispel bad smells because it has a strong smell.